text.__SUMMARY__:
Corymbia deserticola is a member of the genus Corymbia native to Western Australia and the Northern Territory.The tree is a mallee and typically grows to a height of 2 to 6 metres (7 to 20 ft). It has rough tesselated bark and produces yellow-cream flowers.There are two recognised subspecies:

Corymbia deserticola subsp. deserticola
Corymbia deserticola subsp. mesogeotica
